==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Carbonade
<hw>Car"bo*nade</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Carbonadoed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Carbonadoing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cut (meat)
across for frying or broiling; to cut or slice and broil.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A short-legged hen daintily <qex>carbonadoed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bean. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cut or hack, as in fighting.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll so <qex>carbonado</qex> your shanks.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carbonado</ent>⟦br⟧
